    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-07-16T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-07-16T17:00:00-05:00" n="255"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d255">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.154/237: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-07-16T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 16, 1930—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>49. Third numbered paragraph your telegram 46, July 11, 11 a.m. and Department’s
                    mail instruction 31, July 1.</p>
                <p>The Director General of the Pan American Union has just informed the
                        Department<note n="3" xml:id="d255fn3">Letter of July 14; not
                        printed.</note> that the Minister of Panama in Washington has apprized the
                    Pan American Union of the fact that his Government desires the cooperation of
                    this Government in the projected reconnaissance survey of the Panamanian section
                    of the proposed Inter-American Highway.</p>
                <p>Please inform this Government’s cooperating highway engineers and officially
                    introduce them to the appropriate Panamanian authorities in order that the
                    engineers may properly make available this Government’s cooperation.</p>
                <pb facs="0368" n="288" xml:id="pg_288"/>
                <p>The Director General also states that, as reported in the fourth numbered
                    paragraph of your telegraphic despatch, he has been informed that the Government
                    of Panama is prepared to offer adequate office accommodations for the
                    engineers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
